Attaching a Volume to an Instance:

# list the volumes
  -> lsblk

# check if the volume has any data
  -> sudo file -s /dev/xvdf

# format the volume as ext4
  -> sudo mkfs -t ext4 /dev/xvdf
  
# create a directory
  -> mkdir /myexternalvolume

# mount our EBS to our directory
  -> sudo mount /dev/xvdf /myexternalvolume

# go to directory and verify size and free space
  -> cd /myexternalvolume
  -> echo "hello" > hello.txt
  -> df -h .

# to unmount
  -> unmount /dev/xvdf

# backup fstab file
  -> sudo cp /etc/fstab /etc/fstab.bak

# add an entry into our fstab file
  -> cat /etc/fstab
  
# add this line: (/dev/xvdf     /myexternalvolume     ext4     defaults,notail     0    0)
  -> sudo nano /etc/fstab
  
# reboot the system
  -> sudo reboot -h
  
# verify for error after ssh it again
  -> sudo mount -a
  
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Resizing the Volume:

# use lsblk to check the disk size
  -> lsblk

# see how the system sees our drive
  -> df -h

# resize the partition
  -> sudo resize /dev/xvdf

